;; kamado 竈 — seed refining graph (ADR-2606051500)
;; vocabulary: 00-contracts/schemas/refining-ontology.kotoba.edn
;;
;; THREE FACES in one graph:
;;   A. :refinery/* :unit/* :outage/*  — OBSERVED existing assets (incl. fossil ones;
;;      observation is not operation). Supersedes legacy `oil-refining` Cypher actor.
;;   B. :decommission/*  — §2(d) robotics wind-down/convert plans for existing fossil assets.
;;   C. :synthesis/* :carbon/*  — closed-loop carbon refining designs (G1 feedstock).
;;
;; INVARIANT (G1): every :synthesis/feedstock-class is a member of :feedstock/class
;;   allowed set; NO record carries :fossil-virgin-crude as a synthesis feedstock — the
;;   data model cannot hold a fossil-fed refining design (see schema + feedstock_guard.py).
;;
;; SOURCING (G7): every node carries :*/sourcing. BOUNDED illustrative seed. Refinery
;;   names/locations are matters of public record; throughput/status :representative.
;;   Absence of an asset = "not yet ingested", NOT "does not exist". A refinery here is
;;   an OBSERVED public asset operated by an org — NEVER a target (G4).

[;; ───────────────────── A. observed assets (public; observation ≠ operation) ─────────────────────
